title: Mastering Stress - Crafting Your Own Toolbox
content:
First I want to make it very clear that I am not a professional nor am I "traditionally educated" in this field. I am but a person with a lot of time on his hands to educate himself through science and self testing to figure out what works for me & why it works on me.
Having been in LEC for a while now where the environment and schedule is at a very intense level, having these tools to my disposal has immensely helped me.
Mastering stress has changed my life and I would like to believe that it will be able to change yours as well.

1) What is stress & why is it important to understand?
- Stress is what keeps you going and it's what makes you push forward in life.
Example: If you are hungry -> You will automatically seek food and your body will up stress levels.
It's important to understand because it allows you to control your mind if you have the right tools to deal and up stress levels.
If you use your tools correctly you can find yourself lowering stress when you are in a situation of immense stress through the tools you wil learn about in this post.
If you use the tools correctly you can also find yourself upping stress levels when you find yourself sleepy and unmotivated to for example -> go to the gym, having to perform, having to do any sort of task that might require a little bit of an extra push.

In this post you will learn about tools I have been using for myself and my students as well as FNC players themselves.

In my personal opinion being able to master stress is the single most effective tool for having an effective lifestyle.

2) Is stress bad?
Firstly stress is a good thing as long as it does not become chronical & debilitating.
If you are able to regulate your stress levels you are able to stay within the good margins of stress and therefor it is ESSENTIAL that you educate yourself.

Alright enough talk from my side, under this text you will find tools & videos to explore that will help you become a better person & a better player. I HIGHLY recommend that you sit down and take your time with this, don't finish in 1 day.

Make it your personal mission to master stress
Make it your personal mission to have tools to regulate stress as you desire

- Tools -
1) Andrew Huberman "Tools for managing stress & anxiety" : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ntfcfJ28eiU 
-> My own notes from watching https://docs.google.com/document/d/1yHbjpMw4ptBMzHrOro06rrT9GcLKe2HRU0XIN0OxCKg/edit?usp=sharing
2) My presentation for the FNC boys (Only for your own inspiration as you were not there you will be unable to understand 50% of context) https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1ElgbDftyGuEN8thxT9GrnL5pxg8H9kWoJF8CiHvBnWo/edit?usp=sharing
3) Wim Hof breathing for upping stress levels https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tybOi4hjZFQ&t

- Example of a Toolbox -
Upping stress
1) Wim hof breathing
2) Dragon breath
3) Playing Spikeball
4) Putting your face in ice cold water

Lowering stress
1) Physiological Sigh
2) NSDR > Non-sleep deep rest
3) The long exhale
And many many more, what's important is that you understand the concept and you are now ready to play around with the idea of crafting your own toolbox and finding tools that work for you.
What works for me might not work for you, we are all individuals and we all have different needs and things we like/dislike too do.

If you have any questions regarding anything in this post you can drop a comment below, enjoy the content.

title: Habit Stacking & Setting Yourself Up For Success
content:
Creating good habits is the key to having success both in & out of game but how do you do that?

You do it through simple steps and having the right systems and once you connect that to awareness and understanding of your surroundings you will be in a good situation.

The best way I know to create and sustain good habits is to do "Habit stacking"

What is habit stacking?
Habit stacking is when you connect good habits together to create a chain of good habits that once done enough they will subconsciously connect with each other and eventually become your new autopilot.

I recently read Atomic Habits by James Clear, this book is one of the keys to unlocking good habits and understand what it actually means, it is sadly not as simple as "just go to the gym bro" & "just eat healhy dude"

Connected to this text I have given you the teory behind habit stacking and an example of a habit routine of mine.
This is the extreme levels of habit stacking and your own habit stacking does not have to look similar.
Next to that that I have linked all my notes from reading the book that you can hopefully get some inspiration for yourself.

Habit stacking gives you direction and a chance to be consistent in your life.
It is not about disciplin, it's about having the right systems and setting yourself up for success.
